<td width="35" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" align="left" valign="top">
<div align="left"><img src="themes/Vazaelle/images/lefttop.gif" width="17" height="17" border="0"  alt=""></div>
</td>
<td width="100%" valign="top" align="center" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width="100%" border="0"><tr><td valign="top" width="85%">
<br><table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0"><tr><td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="5"><tr><td>
<img src="themes/Vazaelle/images/note_icon.gif" width="14" height="15" alt="*" border="0" align="absmiddle">
<font class="pn-normal"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=3">Site Updates</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=14&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">Site Updates [Sun, Jan 12, 2003 : 1930]</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Posted Jan 12, 2003 - 04:15 AM</font><hr size="1">
<div align="right"><b>
<font class="pn-sub"><a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Recommend_Us&amp;file=index&amp;req=FriendSend&amp;sid=14"><img src="images/global/friend.gif" border="0" alt="Send this story to a friend"></a> Email this to a friend&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="pn-normal" href="print.php?sid=14"><img src="images/global/print.gif" border="0" alt="Printer friendly page"></a> Print this story</font></b></div><p>
<font class="pn-normal">
<br><br>
<font class="pn-art"><a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=&amp;topic=6"><img src="images/topics/topicnews.gif" border="0" Alt="News" align="left" hspace="5" vspace="5" ></a>
I'm just <i>slightly</i> overdue for some updates, so here goes!<br />
<br />
- Layout Changes<br />
- Bugs in the Forums<br />
- <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/~xorrin/" title="Xorrin Aarikis" target="_blank">Xorrin</a> returning to <a href="http://www.EverQuest.com/" title="EverQuest™" target="_blank">EQ</a>?<br />
<BR><BR><H5>Layout Changes</h5><br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	As you can see, there are some minor layout changes to the site.  Most noticeable, however, is the new layout of the Main Menu.  What does this all mean?  It means BIG changes are on the way for Vazaelle.NET!<br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	The original plans for the site were to separate everything.  Vazaelle.NET was to be a generic site for the Vazaelle server in general.  Back in the days before Vazaelle.NET, 2 sites existed...nato-vazalle for the Alliance, and kgm-vazaelle for my Guild.  When I bought this server, I had problems with my former hosting company, FREEBOOST.COM.  The owner Jeff refused to release the domains to me even though I owned them.  He had somehow locked them with his registrar, even though I owned them on a different one.  As a result, I was forced to register a NEW domain, Vazaelle.NET.  I have since regained control of nato-vazaelle, but kgm-vazaelle was forever lost to an online casino – bastards!<br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	Since I own the server, I decided to offer free web space to any <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="N.A.T.O." target="_blank">NATO</a> Guild who needed it.  I would also provide web space to other <a href="http://www.EverQuest.com/" title="EverQuest™" target="_blank">EQ</a> sites for very reasonable rates.  NATO members would be able to register their own domain.  Guilds from the Vazaelle server would also have the ability to use a sub-domain when linked from the Vazaelle.NET site.<UL><LI>Vazaelle.NET would be home to the generic site for the Vazaelle server as a whole.<LI>KGM.Vazaelle.net would be home to the <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="Knights of the Green Mist" target="_blank">Knights of the Green Mist</a> guild site.<LI>NATO.Vazaelle.NET would be home to the Norrath Alliance Treaty Organization site.<LI>NATO members would be able to use URLs such as nv.vazaelle.net, thor.vazaelle.net, and rov.vazaelle.net.  Each site would be completely separate from the other.</UL><P ALIGN="justify">	So, what does this have to do with the menu, you ask?  Simple…  It’s the first step in separating the NATO and <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="Knights of the Green Mist" target="_blank">KGM</a> sites!  The software that this site runs on, PostNuke (PN), supports Multi-Site installations.  What this allows the developer to do is tie certain aspects of the different sites together, while still keeping the core separate.  For example, users would register at Vazaelle.NET (or any sub-site).  This single registration would carry to all other instances of the PN chain…. one registration, one log-in!  Then, each separate site Admin could define permissions for that particular site…. thus allowing the Admin for xyzguild.vazaelle.net to promote his users permissions while not affecting the permissions of the same user on abcguild.vazaelle.net or nato.vazaelle.net.  Pretty nifty, huh?   So why wait for PN 8.0, rather than moving forward with the 7.2.x upgrade?  Security for one…but the main reason is functionality.  The PN developers have saved the BEST new features for the 8.x rollout.<br />
<H5>Bugs in the Forums</h5><br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	Been getting a lot of questions about configuration, customization, and general use of the forums lately.  I've also been noticing a lot of people poking around in areas they really shouldn't be.  This really isn't a major issue, but does warrant some attention.<br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	First, customization/features:  The forums are run using phpBB 1.14.  I have spent TONS of time and energy researching and trying out the MANY different bulletin board packages out there.  I've even considered ezboards, but decided that they really did need to be an actual part of the site.  I boiled my final choices down to 2 systesm...  ikonboard, and phpBB.  I personally like the ikonboard better, as far as overall features go...but it does not play well with other features of the site, and the administration of it is a little sloppy.  phpBB offered simpler navigation and just-as-powerful features, plus it tied in perfectly with the site...right down to using the site theme, in stead of having to build a new one from scratch to make it match.  The only problem is, at the time the site was installed (and in my haste to get the forums up and running before I moved to the other side of the planet), the version that got installed was not complete.  We are currently running a &quot;beta&quot; of sorts...it is a 100% from-scratch rewrite of phpBB specifically for PostNuke - NOT a port of an already working system meant to stand alone.  This allows more functionality and integration with the core PN site... ie: You register and log in once, rather than once on the site, and again on the forums.  It also ties directly in to the user security system - access and permissions, making user administration easier.  Version 2 of phpBB has all that are currently allowing everyone to see, read, and post in any forum (regardless of their access level) fixed and will be installed in the next upgrade to the site's core software.  What I ask of you for now is to please be patient with the forums, and please <i>do not post where you <a href="http://www.daughtersofnorrath.com/" title="Daughters of Norrath" target="_blank">don</a>'t belong!</i>  Specifically - <b>if you are not a member of the Alliance Council (a guild leader of a NATO member guild), please do not post there!!!</b><br />
<H5>Xorrin returning to EQ?</h5><br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	I wish.  Ok, so I FINALLY get my computer after the movers lost everything I own for 4 months.  And it even made it here AFTER the Typhoon, so it's not damaged!  I managed to save up the money to get PoP and SoV for my 2nd account...in all, I spent over $400 in EQ software upgrades alone, thanks to the high cost of living here!  Each copy was $134, plus a few extra toys I picked up...  (remember that little PayPal donation button on the main page?  *lol*  Happy Birthday, to meeeeee......  *hint*...yes, today is my B-day, for real!)  Now all I have to do is get connected to the internet, right?  Hrmm...<br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	If it were that easy, I would have been online on Friday.  You see, the phone company says they can &quot;hook me up&quot; within 2 hours of me calling them.  That is, if the phone line is working...  BUT, since my house took a lightening strike some time before I moved into it, ALL the phone lines are fried.  We're talking crispy black lines that turn to dust when you touch them!  And not just the lines inside (yes, every outlet in every room!), but also the box on the side of the house, the lines under ground going to the main junction box for the street....and, yes, even insde the junction  box itself!  All of it - fried - needs to be replaced.<br />
<P ALIGN="justify">	No big deal.  I can do that in a weekend.  *IF* I could find a place on this island that sells spools of phone line and connection boxes!  Why won't the phone company do it?  They will....in May or June...for $80/hour.  They only maintain the lines going from their switch TO the junction box...not the box itself or anything between it and your phone on the wall.  (remember that nifty little PayPal donation button on the main page?  Happy birthday, to meeee.....  have I mentioned how expensive stuff is here on Guam?  *hint*)  Really, I hate to beg...but it's pretty bad out here....anything helps...even $5...  I'm already paying over $150 just to maintain this web site.  lol...not to mention my monthy EQ fees...which I cannot play...  In the 3+ years I've been playing EQ, I think I've only been able to actually get on it about 2 of them...even though I've been paying all along.  /sigh...think Verant will pay the phone company to fix me up?  lol  They can afford it.    Oh...DSL...to be hooked up within 1 week of the phone getting turned on...depends on how long it takes the ISP to do their paperwork...since the phone company was sued by AT&amp;T and cannot sell DSL to the public.  Did you know AT&amp;T doesn't even exist on Guam?  Nifty how they can do that, huh?<br />
<br />
I had more to write, but forgot it all.  lol...look for an edit some time when my brain returns to me.  ;)</font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top">
